<i>adverb</i>: 호젓이 [호저시], 평온히 [평온히], 차분히 [차분히], 조촐히 [조촐히], 조용히 [조용히], 조용조용 [조용조용], 잠잠히 [잠잠히], 잔잔히 [잔잔히], 은근히 [은근히], 은근슬쩍 [은근슬쩍], 쓱 [쓱], 스르르 [스르르], 솔솔 [솔솔], 소르르 [소르르], 소록소록 [소록쏘록], 새근새근 [새근새근], 살짝살짝 [살짝쌀짝], 살살 [살살], 묵묵히 [뭉무키], 나직이 [나지기], 나지막이 [나지마기], 그윽이 [그으기], 가만히 [가만히], 가만 [가만] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt>호젓이 [호저시]</dt><br>
<dd>1. quietly; tranquilly</dd><br>
<dd>외딴 곳에 있어 고요하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Quietly, being in a remote area.</dd><br>
<dd>2. quietly; in a solitary or lonely manner</dd><br>
<dd>거추장스럽지 않고 홀가분하거나 쓸쓸하고 외롭게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being lighthearted without being bothered by something, or being lonely and cheerless.</dd><br>
<dt>평온히 [평온히]</dt><br>
<dd>calmly; quietly; serenely</dd><br>
<dd>걱정이나 탈이 없고 조용하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Quietly without any worries or troubles.</dd><br>
<dt>차분히 [차분히]</dt><br>
<dd>quietly; composedly</dd><br>
<dd>마음이 가라앉아 조용하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of being composed and quiet.</dd><br>
<dt>조촐히 [조촐히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. cozily</dd><br>
<dd>작지만 아담하고 깨끗이.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being small but petite and clean.</dd><br>
<dd>2. demurely</dd><br>
<dd>행동이나 행실 등이 깔끔하고 얌전히.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being refined and dignified in behavior or deed.</dd><br>
<dd>3. neatly; simply</dd><br>
<dd>외모나 모습 등이 깨끗하고 멋이 있게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being neat and classy in appearance or looks.</dd><br>
<dd>4. quietly; simply</dd><br>
<dd>조용하고 간단하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being quiet and simple.</dd><br>
<dt>조용히 [조용히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. quietly</dd><br>
<dd>아무 소리도 들리지 않게.</dd><br>
<dd>With no sound being heard.</dd><br>
<dd>2. quietly</dd><br>
<dd>말이 적고 행동이 얌전하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being restrained in speech and gentle in behavior.</dd><br>
<dd>3. quietly</dd><br>
<dd>문제가 없이 평안하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Peacefully and without problems.</dd><br>
<dd>4. calmly</dd><br>
<dd>감정이 가라앉아 마음이 평안하게.</dd><br>
<dd>With peace of mind and emotions calmed down.</dd><br>
<dd>5. quietly</dd><br>
<dd>바쁘지 않고 한가하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being free and not busy.</dd><br>
<dd>6. quietly</dd><br>
<dd>남들에게 드러나지 않게 숨어서.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being hidden and not revealed to others.</dd><br>
<dt>조용조용 [조용조용]</dt><br>
<dd>quietly; softly</dd><br>
<dd>말이나 행동이 시끄럽지 않고 매우 얌전한 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of not being loud and very gentle in speech or behavior.</dd><br>
<dt>잠잠히 [잠잠히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. silently; still</dd><br>
<dd>분위기나 활동 등이 시끄럽지 않고 조용히.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of an atmosphere, activity, etc., being quiet, not noisy.</dd><br>
<dd>2. silently; quietly</dd><br>
<dd>말없이 가만히.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of being still without saying anything.</dd><br>
<dd>3. calmly; still</dd><br>
<dd>파도나 바람 등이 움직이지 않고 조용히.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of waves, wind, etc., being quiet without moving.</dd><br>
<dt>잔잔히 [잔잔히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. calmly; tranquilly; quietly</dd><br>
<dd>바람이나 물결 등이 심하지 않고 움직임이 거의 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of the wind, a wave, etc., being still and not severe.</dd><br>
<dd>2. serenely; tranquilly; calmly</dd><br>
<dd>분위기가 고요하고 평화롭게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of an atmosphere being silent and peaceful.</dd><br>
<dd>3. calmly; serenely</dd><br>
<dd>표정이나 태도 등이 차분하고 평온하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of one's look, attitude, etc., being composed and peaceful.</dd><br>
<dd>4. gently</dd><br>
<dd>소리가 조용하고 부드럽게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of a sound being quiet and soft.</dd><br>
<dt>은근히 [은근히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. constantly and slowly</dd><br>
<dd>야단스럽지 않고 꾸준하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Steadily but not too strongly.</dd><br>
<dd>2. tastefully; delicately</dd><br>
<dd>정취가 그윽하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Exquisitely.</dd><br>
<dd>3. quietly; secretly</dd><br>
<dd>행동 등이 드러나지 않고 은밀하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of behaving secretly so that others do not notice.</dd><br>
<dd>4. inwardly</dd><br>
<dd>겉으로 나타내지는 않지만 속으로 생각하는 정도가 깊고 간절하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of thinking about something deeply and sincerely even though one does not reveal it.</dd><br>
<dt>은근슬쩍 [은근슬쩍]</dt><br>
<dd>quietly; secretly; by stealth</dd><br>
<dd>드러나지 않게 슬쩍.</dd><br>
<dd>In such a stealthily manner that something is not noticed.</dd><br>
<dt>쓱 [쓱]</dt><br>
<dd>1. on the quiet; by stealth; quietly</dd><br>
<dd>소리 없이 슬그머니 내밀거나 들어가는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the movement of pushing something out or going into somewhere quietly and stealthily.</dd><br>
<dd>2. stealthily; furtively</dd><br>
<dd>눈에 띄지 않게 슬쩍 사라지는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the movement of vanishing stealthily so that others do not know.</dd><br>
<dd>3. quickly</dd><br>
<dd>빨리 지나가는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the movement of passing quickly.</dd><br>
<dd>4. lightly; deftly</dd><br>
<dd>슬쩍 문지르거나 비비는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the motion of rubbing or wiping something lightly.</dd><br>
<dd>5. quickly and quietly</dd><br>
<dd>슬쩍 행동하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing a person acting quickly and quietly.</dd><br>
<dt>스르르 [스르르]</dt><br>
<dd>1. of itself</dd><br>
<dd>묶이거나 뭉쳐 있던 것이 힘없이 풀리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner that something tangled or lumped is gently disentangled by itself.</dd><br>
<dd>2. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>얼음이나 눈 등이 저절로 녹는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing snow, ice, etc., melting away.</dd><br>
<dd>3. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>잠이 살며시 오거나 눈이 천천히 감기는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing someone falling asleep or his/her eyes being closed slowly.</dd><br>
<dd>4. quietly</dd><br>
<dd>소리 없이 천천히 움직이는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing someone or something moving slowly and quietly.</dd><br>
<dd>5. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>힘이나 기운, 어떤 감정 등이 약해지거나 없어지는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of power, energy, a certain feeling, etc., weakening or disappearing.</dd><br>
<dt>솔솔 [솔솔]</dt><br>
<dd>1. smoothly</dd><br>
<dd>물이나 가루 등이 틈이나 구멍으로 조금씩 새어 나오는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing water, powder, etc., coming through a crack or hole little by little.</dd><br>
<dd>2. gently</dd><br>
<dd>바람이 부드럽게 부는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the wind blowing softly.</dd><br>
<dd>3. lightly</dd><br>
<dd>가는 비나 눈이 잇따라 가볍게 내리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing a fine rain or snow falling lightly.</dd><br>
<dd>4. fluently; smoothly</dd><br>
<dd>말이나 글이 막힘없이 잘 나오거나 써지는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of speaking or writing without hesitation.</dd><br>
<dd>5. smoothly</dd><br>
<dd>묶이거나 엉킨 실이나 끈이 쉽게 잘 풀리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing a tangled or bound thread or string disentangling easily.</dd><br>
<dd>6. easily</dd><br>
<dd>해결하기 어려운 일이나 문제가 쉽게 풀리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of a knotty or difficult problem being solved easily.</dd><br>
<dd>7. lightly</dd><br>
<dd>가볍게 냄새가 나거나 연기가 피어오르는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of a smell or smoke rising lightly.</dd><br>
<dd>8. quietly</dd><br>
<dd>재미가 은근히 나는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of feeling interested quietly.</dd><br>
<dd>9. slowly; quietly</dd><br>
<dd>잠에 조금씩 빠지는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of falling asleep slowly.</dd><br>
<dt>소르르 [소르르]</dt><br>
<dd>1. smoothly; readily</dd><br>
<dd>얽히거나 뭉친 물건이 쉽게 잘 풀리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing a tangled thing unwinding easily.</dd><br>
<dd>2. gently</dd><br>
<dd>바람이 천천히 부드럽게 불어오는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the wind blowing slowly and softly.</dd><br>
<dd>3. quietly</dd><br>
<dd>물이나 가루 등이 조용히 부드럽게 새어 나오는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing water, powder, etc., coming through something quietly and softly.</dd><br>
<dd>4. quietly</dd><br>
<dd>살며시 졸음이 오거나 잠이 드는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing one falling asleep or dozing off quietly.</dd><br>
<dt>소록소록 [소록쏘록]</dt><br>
<dd>1. quietly; peacefully</dd><br>
<dd>아기가 포근하고 곱게 자는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the state of a baby sleeping comfortably and adorably.</dd><br>
<dd>2. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>비나 눈 등이 조용히 내리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the state of rain or snow falling quietly.</dd><br>
<dt>새근새근 [새근새근]</dt><br>
<dd>1. in a gasp</dd><br>
<dd>고르지 않고 가쁘게 자꾸 숨 쉬는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when gasping unevenly and repeatedly, or describing one in this state.</dd><br>
<dd>2. quietly; gently</dd><br>
<dd>어린아이가 깊이 잠들어 조용하게 자꾸 숨 쉬는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when a child makes quiet, breathing sounds repeatedly in his/her sleep, or to make such sounds repeatedly.</dd><br>
<dt>살짝살짝 [살짝쌀짝]</dt><br>
<dd>1. stealthily; furtively</dd><br>
<dd>다른 사람이 보지 못하게 잇따라 재빠르게.</dd><br>
<dd>Quickly in succession so that others cannot see.</dd><br>
<dd>2. lightly</dd><br>
<dd>힘을 들이지 않고 잇따라 가볍게.</dd><br>
<dd>Lightly in succession without much effort.</dd><br>
<dd>3. slightly</dd><br>
<dd>심하지 않게 아주 약간씩.</dd><br>
<dd>Bit by bit and not much.</dd><br>
<dd>4. quietly; furtively</dd><br>
<dd>드러나지 않게 잇따라 가만히.</dd><br>
<dd>Quietly in succession so that others do not know.</dd><br>
<dt>살살 [살살]</dt><br>
<dd>1. gently</dd><br>
<dd>물 등이 천천히 고루 끓는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of water, etc., boiling slowly and evenly.</dd><br>
<dd>2. comfortably</dd><br>
<dd>바닥이 고루 더운 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of the floor being evenly warm.</dd><br>
<dd>3. quietly</dd><br>
<dd>작은 벌레 등이 소리 없이 기어가는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of a small insect, etc., crawling without making noise.</dd><br>
<dd>4. gently</dd><br>
<dd>조심스럽게 움직이는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner in which one moves something or does something carefully.</dd><br>
<dd>5. gently</dd><br>
<dd>머리나 꼬리 등을 좌우로 가볍게 흔드는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of lightly shaking one's head, tail, etc. left and right.</dd><br>
<dt>묵묵히 [뭉무키]</dt><br>
<dd>silently; quietly</dd><br>
<dd>말없이 조용하게.</dd><br>
<dd>Quietly without saying a word.</dd><br>
<dt>나직이 [나지기]</dt><br>
<dd>1. rather low</dd><br>
<dd>위치나 높이가 조금 낮게.</dd><br>
<dd>At a rather low height or location.</dd><br>
<dd>2. quietly; in a whisper</dd><br>
<dd>소리가 조금 낮고 조용하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a rather low and quiet voice.</dd><br>
<dt>나지막이 [나지마기]</dt><br>
<dd>1. rather low</dd><br>
<dd>위치나 높이가 조금 낮게.</dd><br>
<dd>At a rather low height or location.</dd><br>
<dd>2. quietly; in a whisper</dd><br>
<dd>소리가 조금 낮고 조용하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a rather low and quiet voice.</dd><br>
<dt>그윽이 [그으기]</dt><br>
<dd>1. quietly; intimately</dd><br>
<dd>마음에 주는 느낌이 깊고 평안하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of giving deep and peaceful feelings.</dd><br>
<dd>2. gently; mildly</dd><br>
<dd>인상이나 느낌이 은근하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of looking or feeling soft.</dd><br>
<dt>가만히 [가만히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. quietly; motionlessly</dd><br>
<dd>움직이지 않거나 말 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Without movement or words.</dd><br>
<dd>2. indifferently</dd><br>
<dd>일을 해결하기 위한 어떠한 대책이나 노력 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Without any action or effort to solve something.</dd><br>
<dd>3. deliberatey; carefully</dd><br>
<dd>마음을 차분하게 하고 주의를 기울여.</dd><br>
<dd>With calm and care.</dd><br>
<dd>4. silently</dd><br>
<dd>남이 모르게 조용히.</dd><br>
<dd>Quietly so that others will not notice.</dd><br>
<dt>가만 [가만]</dt><br>
<dd>1. quietly; motionlessly</dd><br>
<dd>움직이지 않거나 말 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Without movement or words.</dd><br>
<dd>2. indifferently</dd><br>
<dd>일을 해결하기 위한 어떠한 대책이나 노력 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>Without any action or effort to solve something.</dd><br>
<dd>3. deliberately; carefully</dd><br>
<dd>마음을 차분하게 하고 주의를 기울여.</dd><br>
<dd>With calm and care.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>